00:59:19.000 --> 00:59:22.000
And then someone shouted that one of the planes was smoking.

797
00:59:22.000 --> 00:59:24.000
Yes, we could all see it.

798
00:59:24.000 --> 00:59:28.000
A faint line of black smoke stretched straight from a mile behind one of them.

799
00:59:28.000 --> 00:59:32.000
And as we watched there were gigantic sweep of flame over the plane.

800
00:59:32.000 --> 00:59:39.000
From nose to tail it disappeared in flame and it slanted slowly down and banked around the sky.

801
00:59:39.000 --> 00:59:46.000
And great wide curves this way and that as rhythmically and graceously gracefully as in a slow motion waltz.

802
00:59:46.000 --> 00:59:57.000
Then suddenly it seemed to change its mind and swept upward steeper and steeper and ever slower until finally it seemed poised motionless on its own black pillar of smoke.

803
00:59:57.000 --> 01:00:02.000
And then just as slowly as it had turned over and dived for the earth.

804
01:00:02.000 --> 01:00:07.000
A golden spearhead on the straight black shaft of its own creation.

805
01:00:07.000 --> 01:00:10.000
And disappeared behind the tree tops.

806
01:00:10.000 --> 01:00:16.000
But before it was down there were more cries of there's another one smoking and there's a third one now.

807
01:00:16.000 --> 01:00:19.000
Shoots came out of some of the planes.

808
01:00:19.000 --> 01:00:23.000
Out of some came no shoots at all.

809
01:00:23.000 --> 01:00:28.000
One of the white silk caught on the tail of a plane.

810
01:00:28.000 --> 01:00:36.000
Men with binoculars could see him fighting to get loose until flames swept over him and then a tiny black dot fell through space.

811
01:00:36.000 --> 01:00:41.000
All alone.

812
01:00:41.000 --> 01:00:43.000
And all that time.

813
01:00:43.000 --> 01:00:48.000
The great flat ceiling of the sky was roofed by other planes that didn't go down.

814
01:00:48.000 --> 01:00:52.000
Plowing their way forward as if there were no turmoil in the world.

815
01:00:52.000 --> 01:00:55.000
Nothing deviated them by the slightest.

816
01:00:55.000 --> 01:01:05.000
They stalked on slowly and with a dreadful paw of sound as though they were seeing only something at a great distance and nothing existed between.

817
01:01:05.000 --> 01:01:16.000
God how we admired those men up there and sickened for the ones who fell.

818
01:01:16.000 --> 01:01:21.000
Incredible.

819
01:01:21.000 --> 01:01:28.000
It is possible to become so enthralled by some of the spectacles of war that man is momentarily captivated away from his own danger.

820
01:01:28.000 --> 01:01:34.000
That's what happened to our little groups of group of soldiers as we stood watching them mighty bombing.

821
01:01:34.000 --> 01:01:38.000
But that benign state didn't last long.

822
01:01:38.000 --> 01:01:48.000
As we watched their crept into our consciousness, a realization that the windrows of exploding bombs were easing back towards us.

823
01:01:48.000 --> 01:01:55.000
Flight by flight instead of gradually forward as the plan had called for.

824
01:01:55.000 --> 01:02:06.000
Then we were horrified by the suspicion that those machines high in the sky and completely detached from us were aiming their bombs at the smoke line on the ground.

825
01:02:06.000 --> 01:02:13.000
And a gentle breeze was drifting the smoke line back over us.

826
01:02:13.000 --> 01:02:16.000
